; UTILITY: VCO — three waveshape families morphing over a timbre input: pulse (varying width),
; triangle<->saw, and resonant noise<->sine. `shape` crossfades between the families.
; morph crossfades over its inputs with the selector as the LAST argument.
; timbre and shape are already 0..VMAX, so they feed morph/width directly.
(def vco (fn (:note :timbre :shape => :out)
  (def pulse  (square note :width timbre))
  (def trisaw (morph (triangle note) (saw note) timbre))
  (def resn   (morph (vcf (noise) 900 3600) (sine note) timbre))
  (<- out (morph pulse trisaw resn shape))))
